This paper proposes a method for knowledge distillation in deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves an adversarial learning process, which is also a popular technique in both fields. The paper also discusses the application of the method to image classification and object detection tasks, which are subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of intermediate representations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using experimental results, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
